sentence: i would like to find a flight from kansas city to salt lake city on [um] delta and arriving at about eight o'clock in the evening [um] could you please tell me the aircraft and the flight number thank you

SELECT DISTINCT  v0.flight_number, '"'||v2.aircraft_code||'"',
 '"'||v0.airline_code||'"', '"'||v3.airport_code||'"', '"'||v4.city_code||'"',
 '"'||v4.city_name||'"', '"'||v5.airport_code||'"',
 '"'||v6.city_code||'"', '"'||v6.city_name||'"', v0.arrival_time,
 '"'||v0.aircraft_code_sequence||'"', '"'||v1.aircraft_code_sequence||'"',
 '"'||v1.aircraft_code||'"', '"'||v0.flight_id||'"' FROM flight v0,
 equipment_sequence v1,
 aircraft v2, airport_service v3, city v4, airport_service v5,
 city v6 
WHERE (((((v0.airline_code = 'DL') AND (((v0.from_airport = ANY v3.airport_code) 
AND ((v3.city_code = ANY v4.city_code) 
AND (v4.city_name = 'KANSAS CITY'))) AND (((v0.to_airport = ANY v5.airport_code) 
AND ((v5.city_code = ANY v6.city_code) 
AND (v6.city_name = 'SALT LAKE CITY'))) AND ((v0.arrival_time >=  1930) 
AND (v0.arrival_time <=  2030))))) AND (v0.aircraft_code_sequence = v1.aircraft_code_sequence)) 
AND (v1.aircraft_code = v2.aircraft_code)) AND ( 1 =  1));
sql: ( SELECT DISTINCT FLIGHT.FLIGHT_NUMBER , AIRCRAFT.AIRCRAFT_CODE FROM FLIGHT , EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCE , AIRCRAFT WHERE ( FLIGHT.AIRLINE_CODE = ' DL ' AND ( FLIGHT . CITY_CODE FROM CITY WHERE CITY.CITY_NAME = ' SALT LAKE CITY ' ) ) AND ( FLIGHT.ARRIVAL_TIME > = 1930 AND FLIGHT.ARRIVAL_TIME < = 2030 ) ) ) ) AND FLIGHT.AIRCRAFT_CODE_SEQUENCE = EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCE.AIRCRAFT_CODE_SEQUENCE AND EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCE.AIRCRAFT_CODE = AIRCRAFT.AIRCRAFT_CODE AND 1 = 1 ) ;
